	<Title>
		Hypothyroidism: Can calcium supplements interfere with treatment?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Calcium supplements can interfere with absorption of levothyroxine, an oral medication used to treat hypothyroidism.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		Can calcium supplements interfere with hypothyroidism treatment?
	</Question>
